HEADWORD: Peseta
<hw>Pe*se"ta</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Sp.]</ety>
<def>A Spanish silver coin, and money of account, equal to about
nineteen cents (ca. 1900), and divided into 100 centesimos. Now replaced
by the euro.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> + <source>PJC</source>]</p>

